info.author: Ruy Asan
classifiers: Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules
info.description:
A library for comparing trees of various objects
            in a way that yields useful "paths" to each difference. Simply
            knowing that two object blobs differ is hardly useful without
            knowing where exactly the differences are located. For text
            blobs, text-diff utilities can solve this problem, but they are
            ill suited for dealing with arbitrary data structures such as
            dictionaries where key order doesn't matter.
info.name: treecompare
info.summary:
Compare complex trees of objects with useful 
      	diff output and fuzzy matching options.
info.html_description:
A library for comparing trees of various objects
in a way that yields useful “paths” to each difference. Simply knowing that two object blobs differ is hardly useful without knowing where exactly the differences are located. For text blobs, text-diff utilities can solve this problem, but they are ill suited for dealing with arbitrary data structures such as dictionaries where key order doesn’t matter.
